<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">May 12, 2025</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-may-12-2025/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-253884 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/AdobeStock_289088454-150x150.jpeg" alt="alien" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://aeon.co/essays/why-alien-languages-could-be-far-stranger-than-we-imagine?utm_source=feedly-feed" class="external" target="_blank">What we can learn about human language (by imagining how aliens communicate)</a></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><a href="https://www.theparisreview.org/blog/2025/05/09/the-hobo-handbook/#more-170730" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">On reading and living <em>Camping</em></span><i><span style="font-weight: 400"> on Low or No Dollars</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400"> (aka The Guide)</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://lareviewofbooks.org/article/trumpian-common-sense-and-the-history-of-iq-tests/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The eugenicist roots of IQ testing</span></a></li>
</ul>
